    stem: "A 71-year-old woman with stable angina presents to the cardiologist for medication review. She takes amlodipine 10mg daily, aspirin 100mg, and atorvastatin 40mg. Her resting HR is 78 bpm and BP is 122/74 mmHg. She reports episodic chest tightness on exertion 2–3 times weekly that resolves with rest. She has no heart failure. She has a history of significant bradycardia on a beta-blocker prescribed 2 years ago (HR dropped to 34 bpm). What is the most appropriate add-on anti-anginal agent?",
