    stem: "A 64-year-old man with hypertension is commenced on ramipril 5 mg daily. After two weeks he develops a persistent dry cough that significantly disturbs his sleep. His blood pressure is now well controlled at 128/78 mmHg. He has no history of heart failure or proteinuric diabetic nephropathy. Which is the most appropriate next step?",
