    stem: `A 70-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department for an ongoing central chest pain that started about 1 hour ago. He has the history of recurrent chest pains that are brought on with exertion and relieved with rest, and type II diabetes mellitus. Further assessment establishes the diagnosis of unstable angina. You start him on aspirin, clopidogrel, heparin, and glyceryl trinitrate. The on-call cardiologist advises that you start him on tirofiban as well if it is not contraindicated. Which one of the following is not a contraindication for tirofiban?`,
