    correctAnswer: "C",
    explanation: `The following are absolute contraindications to ACE inhibitors: history of angioedema regardless of cause (even if not due to ACE inhibitor); pregnancy (due to harm to fetus); bilateral renal artery stenosis; previous allergic reaction to ACE inhibitors. Relative contraindications are: aortic stenosis and hypertrophic cardiomyopathy. A dry cough is a common adverse effect of ACE inhibitors and a main cause of non-compliance and abandonment of treatment; however, neither pre-existing cough nor ACE inhibitor-induced cough is a contraindication to their use.`,
