    correctAnswer: "A",
    explanation: `The absolute contraindications to ACE inhibitors are: pregnancy, previous angioedema following use of ACE inhibitors, and hypersensitivity to a specific ACE inhibitor. ACE inhibitors are drugs of choice in diabetic patients who develop hypertension and are strongly recommended even in normotensive diabetics with microalbuminuria. Although ACE inhibitors are associated with decreased GFR, the benefit of delayed progression to renal failure outweighs the transient reduction in GFR in the long run; significant reduction in GFR is a relative contraindication. Asthma is not a contraindication. Myocardial infarction and heart failure (low ejection fraction) are among the main indications for ACE inhibitors.`,
